---
layout: base.njk
title: Writing
description: Authoritative signal intelligence writing for seed-stage B2B SaaS founders. Frameworks, field-tested theory, and opinionated GTM thinking from Signal Resolution.
permalink: /blog/
---

{% set posts = collections.posts or [] %}
{% set featuredPost = collections.featured[0] or posts[0] %}
{% set visiblePosts = [] %}
{% for post in posts %}
  {% if not featuredPost or post.url != featuredPost.url %}
    {% set visiblePosts = visiblePosts.concat([post]) %}
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% set sidePosts = visiblePosts.slice(0, 2) %}
{% set gridPosts = visiblePosts.slice(2, 8) %}
{% set bottomPosts = visiblePosts.slice(8, 10) %}

<div class="page-header">
  <div class="ph-inner">
    <div class="ph-ew">Signal Resolution · Writing</div>
    <h1 class="ph-hl">THINKING.<br>OUT <em>LOUD.</em></h1>
    <p class="ph-sub">Authoritative frameworks, field-tested signal theory, and the unfiltered GTM thinking that most people aren't willing to publish. No content marketing. Just the ideas.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="filter-bar">
  <div class="fb-inner">
    <span class="fb-label">Filter:</span>
    <button class="filter-btn on" onclick="filter('all',this)">All</button>
    <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filter('icp-methodology',this)">ICP Methodology</button>
    <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filter('signal-theory',this)">Signal Theory</button>
    <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filter('psychographics',this)">Psychographics</button>
    <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filter('founder-gtm',this)">Founder GTM</button>
    <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filter('data-layer',this)">Data Layer</button>
    <div class="search-wrap"><input class="search-input" type="text" placeholder="Search posts..." oninput="search(this.value)"><span class="search-icon">⌕</span></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="blog-main">
  <div class="bm-inner">
    {% if featuredPost %}
    <div class="featured-post rv" id="featuredRow">
      <a href="{{ featuredPost.url }}" class="fp-card" data-cat="{{ (featuredPost.data.category or 'icp-methodology') | slug }}" data-title="{{ featuredPost.data.title | escape }}">
        <div class="fp-badge"><span class="fp-badge-dot"></span>Featured · {{ featuredPost.data.category or 'ICP Methodology' }}</div>
        <div class="fp-title">{{ featuredPost.data.title }}</div>
        <div class="fp-excerpt">{{ featuredPost.data.description or featuredPost.templateContent | striptags | truncate(260) }}</div>
        <div class="fp-meta"><span>{{ featuredPost.date | postDate }} · {{ featuredPost.content | readingTime }}</span><span class="fp-read">Read the post →</span></div>
      </a>
      <div class="fp-side">
        {% for post in sidePosts %}
        <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="fp-side-card" data-cat="{{ (post.data.category or 'signal-theory') | slug }}" data-title="{{ post.data.title | escape }}">
          <div class="fsc-tag"><span class="fsc-tag-dot"></span>{{ post.data.category or 'Signal Theory' }}</div>
          <div class="fsc-title">{{ post.data.title }}</div>
          <div class="fsc-excerpt">{{ post.data.description or post.templateContent | striptags | truncate(190) }}</div>
          <div class="fsc-meta"><span>{{ post.date | postDate }} · {{ post.content | readingTime }}</span><span class="fsc-read">Read →</span></div>
        </a>
        {% endfor %}
        {% for i in range(sidePosts | length, 2) %}
        <a href="/assessment/" class="fp-side-card" data-cat="icp-methodology" data-title="Signal Resolution Assessment">
          <div class="fsc-tag"><span class="fsc-tag-dot"></span>ICP Methodology</div>
          <div class="fsc-title">Why Your ICP Document Is a Hypothesis, Not a System</div>
          <div class="fsc-excerpt">Run the assessment to score your signal system and identify your next GTM move.</div>
          <div class="fsc-meta"><span>Free diagnostic</span><span class="fsc-read">Start →</span></div>
        </a>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="post-grid" id="postGrid">
      {% for post in gridPosts %}
      <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="post-card rv{% if loop.index == 2 %} d1{% elif loop.index == 3 %} d2{% endif %}" data-cat="{{ (post.data.category or 'signal-theory') | slug }}" data-title="{{ post.data.title | escape }}">
        <div class="pc-tag"><span class="pc-tag-dot"></span>{{ post.data.category or 'Signal Theory' }}</div>
        <div class="pc-title">{{ post.data.title }}</div>
        <div class="pc-excerpt">{{ post.data.description or post.templateContent | striptags | truncate(210) }}</div>
        <div class="pc-meta"><span>{{ post.date | postDate }} · {{ post.content | readingTime }}</span><span class="pc-read">Read →</span></div>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
      {% for i in range(gridPosts | length, 6) %}
      <a href="/assessment/" class="post-card rv{% if loop.index == 2 %} d1{% elif loop.index == 3 %} d2{% endif %}" data-cat="signal-theory" data-title="Signal Resolution GTM Framework Placeholder">
        <div class="pc-tag"><span class="pc-tag-dot"></span>Signal Theory</div>
        <div class="pc-title">The GTM Playbook AI Broke — And What Comes Next</div>
        <div class="pc-excerpt">Explore the assessment for a scored breakdown of your current signal model and bottlenecks.</div>
        <div class="pc-meta"><span>Framework brief</span><span class="pc-read">Read →</span></div>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
      <div class="no-results" id="noResults">No posts found. Try a different search or category.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="bottom-layout">
      <div class="bottom-posts">
        {% for post in bottomPosts %}
        <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="post-card rv{% if loop.index == 2 %} d1{% endif %}" data-cat="{{ (post.data.category or 'icp-methodology') | slug }}" data-title="{{ post.data.title | escape }}">
          <div class="pc-tag"><span class="pc-tag-dot"></span>{{ post.data.category or 'ICP Methodology' }}</div>
          <div class="pc-title">{{ post.data.title }}</div>
          <div class="pc-excerpt">{{ post.data.description or post.templateContent | striptags | truncate(200) }}</div>
          <div class="pc-meta"><span>{{ post.date | postDate }} · {{ post.content | readingTime }}</span><span class="pc-read">Read →</span></div>
        </a>
        {% endfor %}
        {% for i in range(bottomPosts | length, 2) %}
        <a href="/assessment/" class="post-card rv{% if loop.index == 2 %} d1{% endif %}" data-cat="icp-methodology" data-title="Pipeline Compounding — Why Signal Accuracy Gets Better the Longer You Run It">
          <div class="pc-tag"><span class="pc-tag-dot"></span>ICP Methodology</div>
          <div class="pc-title">Pipeline Compounding — Why Signal Accuracy Gets Better the Longer You Run It</div>
          <div class="pc-excerpt">A static ICP doesn't improve. A signal system does. Every deal — won or lost — is a data point that refines your model.</div>
          <div class="pc-meta"><span>Sep 2025 · 7 min</span><span class="pc-read">Read →</span></div>
        </a>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      <div class="rv d2" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:2px;">
        <div class="sidebar-cta">
          <div class="sc-kicker">Free Diagnostic</div>
          <div class="sc-title">KNOW YOUR SIGNAL SCORE</div>
          <div class="sc-body">Four minutes. Nine questions. A scored breakdown of your ICP across all four signal layers — plus your buyer state classification.</div>
          <a href="/assessment/" class="sc-btn">Take the Free Assessment →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-cta" style="background:var(--s1);">
          <div class="sc-kicker">Free Ebook</div>
          <div class="sc-title">THE ICP RESOLUTION METHOD</div>
          <div class="sc-body">The complete framework for turning social listening into pipeline intelligence. 142 pages + 4 bonuses. Free.</div>
          <div class="sc-email-form">
            <input class="sc-input" type="email" placeholder="Your email" id="sidebarEmail">
            <button class="sc-submit" onclick="submitSidebar(event)">Get the Free Ebook →</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
